  "prompt": "Which songs are best for shrilled voice?",
  "response": "If you're looking for songs that suit a shrill or high-pitched voice, consider the following genres and artists known for their vocal styles:\n\n### Pop:\n1. **\"Teenage Dream\"** by Katy Perry - Her bright, high-energy vocals fit well for a shrill voice.\n2. **\"Shake It Off\"** by Taylor Swift - Upbeat and playful, it allows for playful vocal embellishments.\n3. **\"Since U Been Gone\"** by Kelly Clarkson - This song has soaring high notes that can highlight a shrill voice.\n\n### Rock:\n1. **\"Barracuda\"** by Heart - Ann Wilson's powerful vocals can be emulated with a high-pitched approach.\n2. **\"Dreams\"** by Fleetwood Mac - The harmonies lend themselves well to higher vocal ranges.\n\n### Musical Theater:\n1. **\"Defying Gravity\"** from *Wicked* - This song is known for its soaring high notes and can showcase a powerful voice.\n2. **\"A Whole New World\"** from *Aladdin* - The duet allows for high, clear notes that can shine.\n\n### Indie/Alternative:\n1. **\"Dog Days Are Over\"** by Florence + The Machine - Florence Welch has a unique voice that often hovers in a higher register.\n2. **\"Young Folks\"** by Peter Bjorn and John - The whistling and playful melodies suit a light, shrill vocal style.\n\n### Songs to Consider for Performance:\n1. **\"I Will Always Love You\"** by Whitney Houston - While it\u2019s a challenging song, the high notes are iconic.\n2. **\"Rolling in the Deep\"** by Adele - It has powerful dynamics that can make a shrill voice stand out.\n\n### General Tips:\n- Choose songs with high energy and upbeat tempos to complement a higher vocal range.\n- Consider focusing on songs that have strong melodies or iconic choruses to shine with a shrill voice.\n\nUltimately, the best choices will depend on your personal style and vocal strengths, so it might be worthwhile to experiment with various songs to see what feels best for you!",
